Narrator: In 1869, when José was only eight years old, he left the comfort and safety of his home in Calamba to continue his studies in the town of Biñan. It was the first time he would live far away from his parents and siblings.
Narrator: The journey was not very long, but for a young boy, it felt like traveling to a completely different world. He left behind the warmth of his mother’s care, the guidance of his father, and the familiar laughter of his family.
Narrator: José felt both excitement and fear. He was eager to learn new things, yet his heart felt heavy as he said goodbye.
Narrator: With courage in his heart and dreams in his mind, he began this new chapter of his life — a journey that would teach him independence, discipline, and strength.
